Python – Data Analysis Projects

This folder contains data analysis projects built using Python, primarily focusing on extracting business insights from raw data.

The goal of these projects is to demonstrate practical analytical skills, including data cleaning, exploration, visualization, and interpretation, using tools such as pandas, matplotlib, and seaborn.

⸻

What you can expect

* End-to-end analysis workflows (from raw data to insights)
* Real-world business-oriented datasets
* Clear structure and readable notebooks
* Focus on interpretation, not just code

⸻

Key topics covered

* Data cleaning and preprocessing
* Exploratory data analysis (EDA)
* Revenue and trend analysis
* Customer behavior and segmentation (e.g. RFM)
* Retention and cohort analysis
* Business insight generation

⸻

Tools used

* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib / Seaborn
* Jupyter Notebook

⸻

Projects

* Online Retail Analysis
    Customer, product, and revenue analysis including RFM segmentation and cohort-based retention insights.

⸻

Each project is contained in its own folder and includes a dedicated notebook with explanations and conclusions.

⸻
